<h1>Accessing Data on Socrata-Powered Datasites</h1>

<div class="alert-box">
  <p>The Socrata Open Data API version 1.0 is in the process of being deprecated and replaced by the new SODA 2.0 API. For more information view <a href="#">SODA 2.0 release announcement</a>. For information on the deprecated SODA 1.0 APIs is available <a href="/deprecated">here</a>.</p>
</div>

<p>All datasets on Socrata-powered datasites are automatically accessible via the SODA API. Every dataset gets its own unique data catalog and API endpoint. Finding the API endpoint is simple - either click on the <code>API</code> link in any 


<p>Using the Socrata Open Data API, it is very easy to retrieve row data from a tabular dataset. To retrieve all of the rows for a given dataset, simply call its <code>rows</code> resource with no parameters: <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows.json") %></p>

<p>For larger datasets, you'll probably want to limit the number of rows you retrieve at any given time. To simply retrieve a limited set of rows from a dataset, use the <code>max_rows</code> parameter: <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows.json?max_rows=5") %></p>

<%# TODO: I really the getByIds hack. We need a workaround %>
<p>You can also use the <code>getByIds</code> method along with a <code>start</code> count and <code>length</code> parameter to "page" data from a dataset. For example: <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows.json?method=getByIds&start=340&length=10") %></p>

<p>If you want to retrieve an even more compact version of the dataset, you can use the <code>row_ids_only</code> parameter to retrieve only the row IDs for rows in the dataset, which you can then later retrieve individually: <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows.json?row_ids_only=true") %>, <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows/152.json") %>. You can even retrieve multiple rows at a time by passing in multiple row IDs: <%= get("https://opendata.socrata.com/api/views/n5m4-mism/rows.json?ids=134&ids=34")%></p>

